
Check Style :-
------------------
1. The Checkstyle Plugin (eclipse-cs) integrates the well-known source code analyzer Checkstyle into the
   Eclipse IDE.
2. Check style is a development tool to help programmers to write java code that adheres to a coding standard.
3. check style is an ideal for projects that wants to enforce a coding standard.
4. check verifies the source code and shows errors which violates the coding standards set for the project.

Example Program :
----------------------

Before CheckList :--
----------------------

public class CheckStyle_program 
{
	public static void main(String args[])
	{
		int val1,val2;
		int add;
		System.out.println("Adding two numbers");
		val1 = 10;
		val2 = 20;
		add = val1 + val2;
		System.out.println(add);
	}

}


After CheckList :--
------------------------

